The paper deals with clustering and classification of text documents, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a bipartite graph and modularity optimization is a technique commonly used in network science and social network analysis (cs.SI), and the algorithm's speed and efficiency make it relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
